Vice President Mike Pence delivered remarks at the Independent Women's Forum in Washington, D.C. during Women's History Month. He celebrated the contributions of women throughout history and highlighted the women serving in the Trump administration. Pence also discussed the administration's efforts to support women in the workforce and expand opportunities for all Americans. He mentioned upcoming initiatives on defense spending, infrastructure, and education reform. Pence concluded by expressing gratitude to the Independent Women's Forum for their work and encouraging continued progress for women in the United States.